sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K861029
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: FadE gene in S. enterica and in E.coli have similar function. Yet it is shown that S-FadE have far better efficiency compared to FadE in E.coli. The original S-FadE gene contains PstI restriction site. This part has already been point mutated (The G at 1983bp was mutated to A). We assebled S-FadE with PfadR (BBa_K861060) hoping it will only be overexpressed when fatty acids concentration is high.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kuanwei Sheng

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PfadR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: PfadR, synthetic promoter with tandem FadR binding site
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: At least to our knowledge, there is no promoter exists in nature that can respond solely to FadR since those promoters are often regulated by glucose concentration or oxidative stress and many other factors. We decided to design an artificial promoter to fulfill this task. Specifically, a tandem FadR binding site in FadL promoter is place downstream of promoter J23110 with 3 base pair overlap. We test its function in M9 medium with oleic acid as sole carbon source in plasmid pSB6A1.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kuanwei Sheng
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. MG1655

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow
